metadata.name: Agents 2.0 #428
metadata.description:
There are more than thousand agents(random). These agents can move in any direction. I have given 3 types of direction. First is single(together) direction, second is multi(against) direction and the last is "No Movement(Direction)". Agents have their  own speed, size, movement smoothness, and turbulence. The art is programmatically drawn using basic shapes, math, random using p5js.

All the agents walks around 100 to 230 steps. All speed, smoothness, waviness, turbulence, size, direction, color are randomly generated.

In this art, I am using 29 color palettes. these palettes are from: https://ronikaufman.github.io/color_pals/

Press s or 'S' to save image in default quality.
Add scale=print& before fxhash in the URL to save image in high quality.
Add scale=print2& before fxhash in the URL to save image in highest quality.

Example:
Before: https://gateway.fxhash2.xyz/ipfs/QmYiErKegzf66TgVB...../?fxhash=ooXFx4Cbn23Sacb...
After: https://gateway.fxhash2.xyz/ipfs/QmYiErKegzf66TgVB...../?scale=print&fxhash=ooXFx4Cbn23Sacb... 

Note: Art can take some minutes to render.

Art: 8/2/2022
Created By: ArtLife
Twitter: https://twitter.com/iamPraveenIN

metadata.name: Adventure #58
metadata.description:
‘Adventure’, inspired by ‘Soundscape’ of ‘The Paper Crane’, brings to fxhash the recreation of landscapes with the use of the lines.

What are the lines?

A line is a continuous brand with a longer length than width, made on a surface, by a moving point. It's one of the seven basic elements of art.

How can the lines be?

Lines can be horizontal, vertical or diagonal; straight or curves, thick or thin. But also simple or single-trace, perceived by a glance or composed of fragments of two or more lines, which to visualize them must displace our eyes in several directions.

Artwork (PNG layers). Randomization is powered by PureSpider template.

metadata.name: Secret Stairways #49
metadata.description:
"Secret Stairways" is a project that uses principles of Cellular Automaton to construct buildings that can remember a castle, villages...Wich I have many inspirations in architecture and buildings from the place I live (Minas Gerais).

This project use only points() and shadows(the colors) in its rendering, the algorithm randoms sorts to 5000-9000 points for each iteration. So rendering time can take a while depending of ammount of points the algo has sorted. 
Can take from 30 seconds to 1 minute to full render, after it the textures are instantly applied.

// 5 Shadow Colors
// 5 Background Colors


Works properly on Chromium based Web Browsers.






-Press "S" to save a .png file of the artwork


This is a project in p5.js



Omar Lobato,
08/03/2022.

metadata.name: BAI #244
metadata.description:
The first blueprint was found in 1947 on the northwestern shore of the Dead Sea.
It has been studied several times.
Numerous theories arose trying to explain its origin.
None of them was decided conclusively.

One year ago, a rare group of waves coming from space was intercepted on earth.
This happened during the 2021 summer.
It was unclear if they were born from natural events.
Dying stars, black holes... Humans tried to find patterns. Find a meaning for them.
None of the analyses made any sense.

Bai was a young physicist and Ph.D. student.
Her mother was a civil engineer working in finance.
Her father was an architect and a generative artist.
She had a personal interest in linguistics and algorithmic art, influenced by her father.
She was the one who managed to decrypt the information using her own algorithms.

Those frequencies were the gate to sets of technical drawings, matching precisely the physical blueprint found in 1947.

It's been a year since the waves were discovered.
No definite conclusions have been made yet regarding their origin or their meaning.
Nevertheless, the number of theories keeps increasing with every new blueprint decrypted.

The frequencies keep passing by the earth.
There is still so much investigation to be carried out.
So many questions to be answered.
Yet, the financial crisis is making the budget for investigation decrease rapidly.
The Institute of Space Sciences is running an initiative to self-fund this project.
Three hundred thirteen open spots can then seize those waves.
Encapsulating them as NFTs.


—--------------------

This project is an attempt to experiment with two main ideas arising from technical plans:

1. The inner beauty of architectural plans, city plans, industrial blueprints, and any other type of documents of that nature. A study of graphic elements like annotations, dashed lines, grids, etc. disposed of in different manners to create aesthetically appealing compositions.

2. How does the viewer analyze and interpret abstract compositions of technical plans? Triggering different thoughts and ideas: A Rorschach test with blueprints instead of ink blots.

—--------------------

All the minters at the first tear of the dutch auction will be able to claim A or B: A being one HD signed print of their blueprint or B their unique 1/1, on top of the NFT minted.

Those unique 1/1s will be pre-curated outputs from this algorithm. Some of the 1/1 parameters could be chosen by the minter: colors, main composition, shapes, density, name of the blueprint... so that the result will be a collaboration between the minter, Ismahelio, and the algorithm itself.

Minters at the second tier of the dutch auction can claim one unique 1/1. The difference with the first tier is that the minter won't be involved in the design process. The piece will be designed and curated by Ismahelio.

If there are any of these 1/1s to be claimed. They will be minted within an Objkt.com collection and airdropped to the minters.

—--------------------
Heavily dense compositions might not load on some mobile devices with insufficient memory.
The quality of the piece on phones and tablets has been decreased programmatically.
Visualize the piece in a powerful enough computer for the best experience.

Click 1: Activate
Click 2: increase speed
1: save 4000x4000 png
2: save 6000x6000 png
3: save 8000x8000 png

Original piece by Ismahelio.
August 2022. Madrid - Cadiz. Spain.
Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Morixels Mega Colab #1 #22
Last Trip #26
metadata.description:
"She had a psychotic break, I thought it was important for you to know", wrote the unknown sender of the email. I asked for more information, but he never replied back. "Who is he? Who are they? What if he's talking about her?", I asked myself. 

She never used social networks, and since I had deleted her number from my phone and never wrote it down, I decided to take the bus and check up on her. I promised myself I wouldn't return, but here I am, on my way to her modest home.

I'm thinking about her paintings, both beautiful and disturbing. She painted a lot of them, all different, albeit following some sort of pattern. 

Now I'm thinking about our last day together. God, I hope she is okay. This trip to her house will be the longest I've ever made. I hope it will be the last.

metadata.name: Kinetograms #431
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.

metadata.name: Whirled Peas #18
metadata.description:
Help us spread “Whirled Peas!”

Whirled Peas is a never-before attempted take on NFT (Non Fungible Tokens), but unlike NFTs that have come before, this will be a collective effort to raise money for vulnerable Ukrainian women, LGBTQIA+ people, and disabled refugees who are displaced and endangered by the war as part of the GISH “Change A Life: Ukraine” charity initiative to benefit Legacy of War Foundation and Random Acts.

This collaborative art piece by Misha Collins and Shawn Kemp is being unleashed into the NFT community as part of GISH (the Greatest International Scavenger Hunt), which runs from July 30 - Aug 6. Minting is open to GISH participants only via rolling whitelist spots through August 6, 2022, but after minting, anyone can purchase a Whirled Peas NFT. After the GISH Hunt ends August 6, 2022 at 10 PM PDT, all additional editions will be burned and no additional art will be generated, so there will be limited numbers of this art piece available.

GISH participants will need the support of the fxhash community who understand how generative art works and who have a few tez(ꜩ)  to donate to the cause, so if you want to help, please find a #WhirledPeas GISH player on social media, hook them up with a few tez(ꜩ) and help them learn about minting on fxhash. 

100% of the mint and 25% of each secondary sale (the maximum portion allowable on the platform) goes to our charity initiative (minus gas and platform fees). Additionally, we ask that anyone collecting this NFT through the week of August 6 do so as a part of our charity campaign and, on your honor, promise to donate 100% of your profits to this charity initiative as well by transferring it to the charity wallet (tz2SBWGZn7mf4UxoPv6tD1HM3sVvFx2EWKtA). Then, re-list it to keep it circulating to help vulnerable Ukrainians — kind of like a virtual game of hot potato, but with NFT art. After August 6, we welcome you to buy and sell it as you normally would, though we still hope you donate some or all of your profits to the cause. Of course, we can’t control what sellers down the chain choose to do, but we are grateful for your support of this charity initiative. Thank you for helping us to help Ukrainians.

Learn More - https://alleditions.art/p/whirled-peas

metadata.name: Alleles #137
metadata.description:
An allele, short for 'allelomorph', is an alternative version of a specific gene.

This collection (which is in no way scientifically accurate), was born out of an exercise in simplicity. Outputs are made up of arrangements of squares in various compositions, yet within that we are free to imagine what they could mean. For some, the resulting shapes might represent DNA strands or atoms. Others might see cells or the building blocks of the hereditary instructions that shape us as individuals. 

A generative genetic report accompanies each output to spark the imagination and attempt to attach further meaning to each composition. Some gene sequences carry mutations, however not all mutations are visually apparent. Please refer to the fxhash features to view the reports accordingly.

Texture is used subtly, so for maximum enjoyment it is recommended that you save and view your outputs at full size in order to best enjoy the details.

Press 'S' to save a 2400 x 3396 px PNG file.
